sub_title: Founder The Travel Tester, The London Tester & The Space Tester
summary:
Nienke Krook is a former school teacher from Amsterdam, working as a freelance content creator and online marketing manager since 2013. She is the founder & publisher of: 

www.thetraveltester.com
Cultural and Creative Travel. Abroad and at Home.

www.thelondontester.com
UK & Ireland Trip Planning. 

www.thespacetester.com
Space Tourism on Earth.

awards:
[{'title': 'Best Room Tour Video #MyMauritius', 'description': 'During the iambassador #MyMauritius ExplorerLab, 30 content creators from 16 countries in four continents were specially selected from more than 390 applications to attend a week full of workshops to improve their blogging, photography and video skills and experience the island and its stunning properties. 

During the awards ceremony on the final night, The Travel Tester was give special recognition in the form of a glass shield produced by a Mauritian artist in the category ‘Best Room Tour Video’. 

The content that we produced was shot at the Four Seasons Resort at Anahita and included a series of Instagram photos, engaging Instagram stories and 6-minute video showcasing the highlights of the resort from a candid viewpoint.', 'issuer': 'Visit Mauritius // iambassador', 'date': {'month': 11, 'day': None, 'year': 2019}}, {'title': 'World Travel Awards Winner #24HoursintheUK 2018', 'description': 'The Travel Tester / The London Tester worked on the award winning digital campaign with iambassador, VisitBritain and VisitEngland to promote round-the-clock activities and experiences across the UK, encouraging Brits to beat the January blues by taking a holiday at home.

The 24 Hours in the UK series of short films, launched by VisitEngland and the tourism organisations of London, Northern Ireland, Scotland and Wales, showcase activities across the UK throughout a 24-hour period. As well as inspiring Brits to take a holiday at home, the campaign asked people to vote for their favourite moment from the trips. 

“This campaign shows that England is bursting with activity not only round-the-clock but year-round, with experiences to suit all interests and ages. With many of us looking for travel inspiration to beat the winter blues, these snapshots of destinations across the country will get Brits booking mood-boosting experiences, driving economic growth from tourism across the country.” - VisitEngland Director Andrew Stokes', 'issuer': 'World Travel Awards > iambassador, VisitBritain & VisitEngland', 'date': {'month': 6, 'day': None, 'year': 2018}}]
